- What's in the future?
- Despite the Kinect system bringing interaction to the physical level, very much interaction still takes place on a flat screen, sometimes in 3D.
The input information stream has improved (the system receives more data), but the output stream has not been particularly good so far.
We're trying to change that, working on really three-dimensional imaging systems based on different technologies, including projective imaging.
We need to bring the computer world into our physical world, make it more real.
However, to do this, it is necessary to know not only the user but also the space around him.
Then we can add virtual objects to the real world in a much more appropriate form.
