"We will discuss all solutions, none excluded, nor a treaty with Nicaragua that would require negotiations with this country", he stressed.
"I hope I can tell President Ortega that we should conduct the negotiations in the most civilized and unambiguous way possible", Santos added.
Santos and Ortega are meeting in Mexico on Saturday to attend the inauguration of President Enrique Peña Nieta.
The EU Defence Ministers met in the framework of the summit in advance to approve the 2013 Action Plan, which seeks to strengthen dialogue and consensus on defence in the region.
The members of UNASUR are Argentina, Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru, Brazil, Uruguay, Venezuela, Chile, Guyana, Suriname and Paraguay, although the latter is currently excluded.
Peru is the interim chairman of this regional bloc.
