And then I said goodbye to one championship -- in 1981, when Jerome Mincy made his BSN debut.
"The team then took over from 'Cuco' Ortiz, who was an excellent leader", Reyes said.
"I remember Gene Bartow, who was a former coach here and was at the University of Alabama at Birmingham at the time, saying to me, "I have a two-foot-tall player for you.
